# Expert Logic & Data Handling

Expert Logic & Data Handling is designed for enterprise-scale systems, adaptive runtimes, and advanced data processing within VariantalX.

> Warning: The features in this document are intended for advanced developers and system architects.

---

## Data Containers

Data Containers store structured information.

```vx
container PlayerData {

    username;
    level;
    experience;
    inventory;

}
```

Access data:

```vx
PlayerData.username;
PlayerData.level;
```

---

## Multi-Layer Containers

Containers may contain nested containers.

```vx
container PlayerData {

    container Statistics {

        level;
        experience;
        rank;

    }

}
```

---

## Data Streams

Data Streams allow continuous processing of incoming information.

```vx
stream PlayerEvents {

    source = Runtime;

}
```

Read stream:

```vx
stream.read<
    PlayerEvents
>;
```

---

## Logic Matrices

Logic Matrices evaluate multiple conditions simultaneously.

```vx
matrix PlayerValidation {

    verified;
    active;
    notBanned;

}
```

Execute:

```vx
matrix.execute<
    PlayerValidation
>;
```

---

## Data Synchronization

Synchronize data across runtimes.

```vx
sync {

    source = RuntimeA;
    target = RuntimeB;

}
```

---

## Parallel Execution

Run multiple operations at the same time.

```vx
parallel {

    loadPlayerData;
    verifyAccount;
    generateSession;

}
```

---

## Expert Variants

Variants may contain independent execution environments.

```vx
variant<Enterprise> {

    runtime.allocate<
        2048MB
    >;

}
```

---

## Runtime Intelligence

Runtime Intelligence adapts logic based on live system conditions.

```vx
runtime.intelligence {

    monitorUsers = true;
    optimizeMemory = true;
    adaptiveScaling = true;

}
```

---

## Data Compression

Reduce memory usage for large datasets.

```vx
compress<
    PlayerDatabase
>;
```

Restore:

```vx
decompress<
    PlayerDatabase
>;
```

---

## Predictive Logic

Predictive Logic estimates future outcomes.

```vx
predict {

    source = PlayerData;
    target = SessionDuration;

}
```

---

## Expert Example

```vx
container PlayerData {

    username;
    level;
    experience;

}

parallel {

    sync<PlayerData>;
    compress<PlayerData>;
    predict<PlayerData>;

}

runtime.intelligence {

    adaptiveScaling = true;

}
```

